benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/invoicePayments/{paymentId}/tags - Remove tags from payment

covered: Valid Deletion: Multiple tests (TC01–TC05) confirm successful removal of tags (204) with and without tagDef, including removal with no tags (TC05).
Error Handling & Boundary Conditions: 400/404/401/503/504 cases covered (TC06, TC07, TC08, TC11, TC12, TC22), including missing header and unauthorized scenarios.
Query Parameter Validation & Variations: Tests cover single/multiple tagDefs (TC02/TC03), invalid tagDef (TC09), not-present tagDefs (TC10), extra param (TC14) and large tagDef sets (TC15).
Data Integrity & Audit: Data consistency check (TC21) and audit logging (TC20).
Performance, Regression, and Compatibility: Performance under load (TC17), regression (TC18), backward compatibility (TC19).
Concurrency: Concurrent removal scenario (TC16) testing race conditions and final state correctness.
gaps: Soft Deletes: No explicit soft-delete semantics test for tag relationships is present.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No tests for rate limiting under high request volumes.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control).
Edge-case: 403 Forbidden test for insufficient privileges not separately covered.
recommendations: Add a dedicated soft-delete semantics test to verify non-permanent removal behavior if relevant.
Introduce rate-limiting tests and throttling scenarios under concurrency and load.
Add caching header validations (ETag / Cache-Control) for GET responses related to tags.
Include a dedicated 403 Forbidden test path for insufficient privileges in addition to 401.
Add an internal server error (500) test scenario to complement the existing 503 service unavailability scenario.
